# Design system

- Before visual code, read `DESIGN.md` and `docs/design_system.md`.
- Feature screens: prefer `CommonPageLayout` (see `docs/design_system.md` § Page shell); avoid new raw `Scaffold` unless FirebaseUI or nav shell.
- Runtime source wins: `AppTheme`, `buildAppMixScope`, `AppStyles`, `UI`.
- Avoid ad-hoc colors, spacing, typography, radii, component states when shared tokens/styles fit.
- Build real workflow/demo first; avoid landing/marketing pages unless required.
- Verify states: loading, empty, error, disabled, offline/sync, success.
- Responsive: no fixed sizes on reflowable UI; `LayoutBuilder` / `MediaQuery` when suitable — `docs/design_system.md` § Responsive layout.
- Cross-platform: widgets must work on mobile, tablet, web, desktop — `docs/design_system.md` § Cross-platform form factors; `flutter-cross-platform-modern`.
- Check mobile/tablet/desktop (and web pointer/focus when applicable) for clipped text, overlap, unstable controls, hidden primary content.
- If `DESIGN.md` changed, run `./tool/check_design_md.sh`.
- If Mix tokens/styles changed, run `./tool/run_mix_lint.sh` plus focused
  widget/app-visible proof where practical.
- Large `lib/` edits: keep files ≤225 lines (`file_too_long`); run
  `./tool/run_file_length_lint.sh` when splitting or adding substantial code.
